    "biography": "<p>10&rsquo; long, serpentine lizards. Unintelligent, but highly magical. Dwell in&nbsp; caverns and twisted brambles.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Surprise:</strong> Characters surprised by a basilisk meet its gaze.</li>\n<li><strong>Petrifying touch: </strong>Anyone touched by a basilisk is turned to stone (Physical save).</li>\n<li><strong>Petrifying gaze: </strong>Anyone meeting a basilisk&rsquo;s gaze is turned to stone (Evasion save). Unless averting eyes or using a mirror, characters in melee are affected each round.</li>\n<li><strong>Averting eyes:</strong> &ndash;4 penalty to hit; the basilisk gains a +2 bonus to attack.</li>\n<li><strong>Mirrors:</strong> The reflection of a basilisk is harmless. Fighting by looking in a mirror incurs a &ndash;1 penalty to attack. If a basilisk sees its own reflection (2-in-6 chance), it must save or be petrified.</li>\n</ul>"
  },
